The '''Hera Borghese''' is a type of sculpture of [[Hera]] named after the owners of its archetype, the [[Borghese collection|Borghese]]. One example is in the [[National Museum of Rome]][http://www.scholarsresource.com/browse/work/6769], whilst others are in the [[Palatine Hill|Palatine Antiquarium]][http://www2.siba.fi/~kkoskim/imbas/roma/imgpage.php?lang=fi&action=3&themeid=mpalatin&imgid=227_006bw] and at the [http://www.areamarinaprotettabaia.it/archeologia.php?id=17 Castello Aragonese Museum] at [[Baiae]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.marmisommersi.com/en/reperti/hera-borghese/|title=Hera Borghese|website=www.marmisommersi.com|access-date=2016-12-09}}</ref>
