ock|website=traditions.cultural-china.com/en/14T8158T12916.html|accessdate=30 April 2016}}</ref> *[[The Scottish Play|Saying the word "Macbeth"]] while inside a theatre *[[Cultural depictions of ravens|Ravens]], crows and [[Magpies#In culture|magpies]] *[[Ouija board]] *[[Thunderstorms]] *[[Greek Orthodox]] priest in the street. It is considered a bad omen to see a priest walking in the street, and superstitious people whisper "ΣΚΟΡΔΑ" (''skorda'' - "garlic") under their breath. *[[Navajo]]: **pointing at a rainbow<ref name=Navajo1>{{cite web |url=http://www.navajocentral.org/navajotaboos/taboos_nature.html |title=Navajo Taboos for Nature, Domestic and Wild Animals |author=Ernest Bulows |date= |work=NavajoCentral.org |accessdate=March 26, 2016}} {{Better source|reason=Not sure who these folks are or how robust their fact-checking is |date=March 2016}}</ref><ref name=Navajo2>{{cite web |url=http://indiancountrytodaymedianetwork.com/2014/07/24/10-things-you-need-know-about-navajos-155993 |title=10 Things You Need to Know About Navajos |author=Alysa Landry |date=July 24, 2014 |work=Indian Country Today Media Network |accessdate=March 26, 2016}}</ref> **throwing rocks into the wind<ref name=Navajo1/><ref name=Navajo2/> **a [[coyote]] crossing one's path<ref name=Navajo1/> heading north<ref name=Navajo2/> **an [[owl]] flying over a house.
