{{Use British English|date=February 2012}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}} {{Infobox comedian | name = Max & Ivan | image =Max & Ivan.jpg | imagesize = 230px | caption = | origin = | nationality = British | medium = Theatre, radio, television | active = 2007-2008, 2011–present | genre = Comedy, [[sketch comedy]], [[theatre]] | subject = | influences = | influenced = | notable_work = The Casebook of Max & Ivan ([[BBC Radio 4]]), The Reunion, [[W1A (TV series)]] | website = [http://www.maxandivan.com/ Max & Ivan official website] | footnotes = |Awards=Panel Prize [[Edinburgh Comedy Awards]] Winners, Best Show [[Edinburgh Comedy Awards]] Nominees, Most Outstanding Show [[Barry Award (for comedy)]] Nominees}}
Max Olesker and Ivan Gonzalez are a British [[Double act|comedy duo]] known collectively as '''Max & Ivan'''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://maxandivan.com/about|title=ABOUT - Max & Ivan|work=Max & Ivan|access-date=2017-03-18|language=en-US}}</ref> They are the creators, writers and stars of the [[BBC Radio 4]] series ''The Casebook of Max & Ivan''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01qynf5|title=The Casebook of Max and Ivan - BBC Radio 4|website=BBC|access-date=2017-03-18}}</ref> and [[Channel 4]] Comedy Blap ''The Reunion.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/comedy-blaps/on-demand/65317-001|title=Comedy Blaps - On Demand - All 4|website=www.channel4.com|language=en|access-date=2017-03-18}}</ref> They also appear together as Ben & Jerry in [[BBC Two]]'s [[W1A (TV series)|W1A]]. The duo met at [[Royal Holloway, University of London]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.royalholloway.ac.uk/dramaandtheatre/yourfuturecareer/graduateprofiles.aspx|title=Graduate Profiles, Royal Holloway University of London|access-date=2018-03-20}}</ref> where they produced the radio show (and later podcast) ''Max and Ivàn: Exposed'' for the college's [[Insanity Radio]] station.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/podcast/insanity-radio-entertainment/id206207649|title=Max and Ivan: Exposed on iTunes|website=iTunes}}</ref> They co-founded London improvised comedy theatre [[The Free Association]]{{Citation needed|reason=no source for them having co-founded|date=September 2018}} and perform live narrative [[sketch comedy]] across the world.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/comedy/news/sxsw-max-and-ivan-fly-the-flag-for-british-comedy-in-texas-8525069.html|title=SXSW: Max and Ivan fly the flag for British comedy in Texas|date=2013-03-07|work=The Independent|access-date=2017-03-18|language=en-GB}}</ref>
== Style and influences == In episode 73 of [[The Comedian's Comedian with Stuart Goldsmith]], Max & Ivan describe their live shows as narrative sketch comedy; writing character-led narratives that feature interweaving plot lines. They perform these multi-character shows with no costume changes and minimal use of props.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.comedianscomedian.com/73-max-and-ivan-live/|title=73 – Max And Ivan (Live)|date=2014-04-17|work=The Comedian's Comedian|access-date=2017-03-19|language=en-GB}}</ref>
Comedy acts that Max & Ivan have cited as influences include [[The League of Gentlemen]], [[Victoria Wood]], [[Little Britain|Lucas and Walliams]], [[Steve Coogan]] and the [[Marx Brothers]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.timeout.com/london/comedy/max-and-ivan-top-ten-comedians|title=Max and Ivan’s top ten comedians|work=Time Out London|access-date=2017-03-19|language=en}}</ref>
